[{"id":"VR857484","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a concave mirror facing to the left with its principal axis shown as a dash line extending to the left of the mirror. A vertical arrow pointing upwards from the principal axis is labeled Object. Also represented on the principal axis are points A, B, C and D as well as points for the Center of Curvature and the Focal point. These appear from left to right in the following order: Point A, Object, Point B, Center of Curvature, Point C, Focal Point, Point D. The distance between the mirror and Focal Point is labeled f. The distance between the focal point and the Center of Curvature is also labeled f. A note indicates the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857484.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An object is in front of a concave mirror of focal length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"f\"><math alttext=\"f\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>f</mi></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. Also shown are the locations of the center of curvature and the focal point for the mirror, as well as four points labeled <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math></span></span>, which are located on the mirrorâ€™s principal axis as follows.</p><ul class=\"unordered_list style:1\"><li class=\"list_item\"><p class=\"list_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> is located a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 f\"><math alttext=\"10 f\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>10</mn><mi>f</mi></math></span></span> away from the mirror.</p></li><li class=\"list_item\"><p class=\"list_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> is located just beyond the center of curvature.</p></li><li class=\"list_item\"><p class=\"list_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\"><math alttext=\"C\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></span></span> is halfway between the center of curvature and the focal point.</p></li><li class=\"list_item\"><p class=\"list_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">D</mi></math></span></span> is located just inside the focal point.</p></li></ul><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following locations for the object would result in the largest <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">real</span> image being formed by the mirror?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR857484_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvar